rComments: This teacher is condescending to student, talk about random stuff, is unprofessional and useless. Avoid at all cost.

Le prof ne sait pas de quoi il parle et raconte des choses qui ne seront même pas sur l'examen de 60%. Il parle de ses problèmes personnels et ses frustrations personnelles. C'est un GPA killer. Ne pas prendre à tout prix. Sa phrase préféré: Allez demander à vos camarades. Je ne réponds pas aux questions en dehors de la classe ni durant la pause.
Avoid at all all all all all all all all cost! You will learn nothing from him and lose everything for your GPA.

Seriously the worst class I've taken in University. Prof will interrupt or stop presentations he finds uninteresting. Condescending to students. No grades or feedback provided during semester, only a final grade. Very unorganized. Talks about random conspiracy theories rather than class material. Final exam is HARD, 100 MCQ on random data and stats

Je ne conseille pas ce prof. Il ne sait pas de quoi il parle, et dit n'importe quoi juste pour passer le cours. Il discute de choses politiques qui ne le regarde meme pas et qui n'ont aucun lien avec le cours. Sa notation est un GPA killer! Avoid at all costs.

Un prof très comique qui sait capter l'attention des étudiants. Bon cours optionnel à choisir puisqu'il n'y a pas de midterm et 10% de la note est la présence aux cours donc si tu assiste aux cours et que tu étudies pour le final tu peux très bien finir avec un A.

I learned almost nothing in this class and forgot half of what I did learn within a week of the final. Probably the laziest prof I've had. Group project assigned in first week, so make friends fast. %60 final, all multiple choice, including questions on random statistics from the slides. Prof believes some anti-vaccine conspiracies, so yeah.
Insightful prof with a huge worldwide experience in the fields of Economics, Finance, and Business. He also teaches at the MBA level. I plan to take the course he teaches there.

Great sense of humour. This prof is highly knowledgeable and has a good grasp on the subject matter of globalization, and on Economics in general. I liked that he stayed neutral when discussions the various flaws of globalization. The final is not difficult if you study for it. Attend all classes; he gives away tips for the final exam.

Il y a pas de livre en particulier pour suivre le cours. Il nous donne une liste de livre qu'il faudrait lire afin de comprendre la matière, donc cela implique beaucoup de recherche. Pas la peine de lui envoyé un email, il a dit qu'il ne va pas les ouvrir ... L'examen final était de 60% de la note final, c'est facile SEULEMENT si t'as étudier.

this prof is just not ready to teach. He talks about students and don't even listen to their presentations(he tells people to go back to their sits and stop the presentation as it is not interesting!!!) the final exam is 100 multiple choices that are not related to what he teaches in class. Very HARD. He is always grumpy and not happy to be there.
The class is interesting but NOT with the prof!!!!!
The prof is very nice but the course is unstructured and unclear.  Unfortunately, I wouldn't recommend anyone taking this course with this prof.

This guy is one of the best profs I have ever had at the University of Ottawa - he teaches you the core ideas underlying International Commerce, with a touch of Economics, Sociology, History and Philosophy, all the while being very clear and eloquent. Wish we had more like him at UOttawa. Study well the notes for the exam (everything is in there!).

Intelligent person with a lot of poise and knowledge - this prof is clearly at the top of his game. The notes, although a bit dense, are very informative (make sure you know the stats!). I found very impressive the fact that he could speak clearly without referring to his notes (what a lot of profs are unable to do!). Good sense of humour.

He knows his stuff and has very funny jokes. Having said that he is kind of lazy and his final only consisted of very tough mcq questions. If you take him, I recommend you pay very close attention in class and write everything down.

Sa matière semblait lui passer vingt pieds au-dessus de la tête. Examen final de 60%, dans lequel il fallait retenir plein de chiffres et de données sans réelle importance. Diapos ultra chargées qui passent rapidement dans un cours qui passe très lentement !

The entire semester he was giving away hints for the exam if you go to class and read his slides its an easy A. He starts speaking in french every once in a while but its mostly jokes. over all its an easy class if you just read the slides.

Only take this class if you have to. Very unstructured, confusing and altogether unorganized. The prof is nice but doesn't speak english very well at all. He is very unclear during letters and with what he expects from you. Final exam is based on random statistics and is really difficult.

The prof. seems nice, but the class is useless unless you like memorizing statistics and stuff. The multiple choice questions were not easy at all in final exams. Don't take this class if you have other choices.
